I would like to add, I recompiled libtensorflow_cc.so with a modified BUILD file with added TensorRT dependency targets, as suggested here. However, when I try to load this target, it complains about the following when running the application:
2018-09-02 20:31:55.750531: F tensorflow/core/common_runtime/device_factory.cc:77] Duplicate registration of device factory for type GPU with the same priority 210
So, I am still unable to run a TensorRT optimized graph using the C++ API. It would be great if someone could elaborate whether this is a current limitation, or a bug etc.

body:
I would like to add, I recompiled libtensorflow_cc.so with a modified BUILD file with added TensorRT dependency targets, as suggested [here](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/50125889/c-tensorflow-api-with-tensorrt/52111461#52111461). However, when I try to load this target, it complains about the following when running the application:
`
2018-09-02 20:31:55.750531: F tensorflow/core/common_runtime/device_factory.cc:77] Duplicate registration of device factory for type GPU with the same priority 210
`
So, I am still unable to run a TensorRT optimized graph using the C++ API. It would be great if someone could elaborate whether this is a current limitation, or a bug etc.
